left_name: Taste of the Wild Pacific Stream Puppy
left_descrtiption: Taste of the Wild - Pacific Stream Puppy is a delicious grain-free delight for any breed of growing dog. This balanced recipe has been developed from the natural diets of dogs in the wild; full of everything your dog could need to live a happy and healthy lifestyle. Sweet potatoes are the carbohydrate source in this dry food; something that is much easier to digest than grains and cereals; which can lead to adverse reactions and make mealtimes an unpleasant experience for sensitive dogs. As well as being a healthy source of carbohydrate; they also provide vital vitamins such as calcium; beta-carotene and iron; and act as a source of dietary fibre. This tasty dish uses fish as its only source of protein; which adds to its already high digestibility. Salmon not only acts as a premium protein but also as a source of omega-3 fatty acids such as DHA; which are known to help with eyesight and brain development; which are naturally of the utmost importance in a growing puppy. They can also keep joints moving smoothly and coat gleaming and in tip-top condition. Inulin; yucca schidigera and chicory all work to promote healthy digestive function. Every ingredient in this food is designed to keep your dog's health at the highest possible standard; providing all necessary nutrients and even acting as a source of antioxidants to increase immune system function. A luxurious culinary delight for even the most sensitive of dogs.Taste of the Wild - Pacific Stream Puppy dry dog food at a glance:Suitable for any breed and ideal for puppies. Ideal for sensitive dogs suffering from dietary intolerance or allergic reactions to particular proteins and/or grain.Mono-source protein: By using just one source of protein; this food becomes extremely well accepted and highly-digestible.With tasty salmon: For premium protein and essential omega-3 fatty acids. Highly-digestible and delicious. Grain-free: Grain can often lead to unpleasant adverse reactions; which is why this food contains none. Grain is also high in carbohydrate; which can lead to innumerable unpleasant issues with health. By avoiding grain; this dry food provides your dog with a healthy all-round nutrition.Omega fatty acids: Omega-3 and -6 fatty acids give your dog healthy skin and glossy coat.Sweet Potatoes: Ultra nutritious and highly-digestible; they are packed full of fibre; as well as being a source of vitamins such as calcium; beta-carotene and iron.Raspberries and blueberries: Contain antioxidants in the form of phytonutrients; to help neutralise free radicals.Tomatoes: Full of vegetable fibre to promote digestion and packed with vitamins and antioxidants; including lycopene and beta-carotene.Free from: Animal and vegetable by-products; waste products from the slaughterhouse and artificial flavourings and colourings. All Life-Stages Nutrition: Taste of the Wild dog food has been designed to continue meeting your dog's needs at every point in its life; according to the AAFCO (Association of American Feed Control Officials) recommendations.Taste of the Wild – Pacific Stream Puppy dog food is ideal for junior dogs and puppies of any breed - dog food just as nature intended.

Omega fatty acids help to keep your dog’s coat glossy and skin healthy. Water used in the cooking process is purified by reverse osmosis; which guarantees safe; sterile water. right_descrtiption: Royal Canin Mini Dermacomfort is a unique food that can help small dogs that suffer from skin irritation. Healthy skin is vital to ensuring your dog’s wellbeing; as it forms a barrier which protects the organs; and prevents the body from drying out. It also protects the body from injury and infections from harmful bacteria; as well as storing fats and vitamins and being an important source of sensory information.Itching; dandruff; a greasy coat or dry skin are all signs that something may be wrong with your dog. These complaints can affect your dog’s overall wellbeing; so they should not be ignored. Royal Canin Mini Dermacomfort has a combination of active ingredients designed to combat skin complaints and improve the skin’s health. Royal Canin Mini Dermacomfort dog food contains a unique combination of nutrients and a patented complex to improve and keep your dog’s fur and skin healthy. After only one month of feeding your dog Royal Canin Dermacomfort you will notice an improvement; with less scratching and itching.Royal Canin Health Nutrition - know and respect your dog's behavioural and nutritional requirements to ensure its wellbeing and health. The benefits of Royal Canin Mini Dermacomfort at a glance:For small dogs with sensitive skinKeeps skin healthySupports the skin’s barrier roleWith valuable omega-3- and omega-6 fatty acids which have a positive effect on skin and furWith selected; highly digestible protein sources which are for dogs with sensitive skinReduces skin irritation and itchingReduces skin issues. Visible results achieved after only one month of feedingLess scratching and itching

right_descrtiption: Royal Canin Golden Retriever Junior dry dog food is made according to a delicious recipe that provides all the nutrients your young dog needs during this important life stage. As they age; junior Golden Retrievers go through a sensitive growth period that can have a significant impact upon their health in later life. Nutritional deficiencies at a young age can lead to a range of health conditions in adulthood; so it is vital that your growing Golden Retriever receives special dietary care. Royal Canin Breed Golden Retriever Junior is the ideal balanced diet for young Golden Retrievers up to 15 months old; helping to protect the health of your dog's joints and provide important support for their natural immune system.Golden Retrievers are well-loved for their friendly and trusting nature; which makes them an excellent family dog. Their distinctive soft and glossy coat features a water-repellent undercoat; which requires particular care and protection. Golden Retrievers also have highly sensitive skin; meaning they need special nutritional support to help strengthen their skin's resistance to allergens and inflammation. Royal Canin Junior Golden Retriever has been developed with these breed characteristics in mind; so you can be sure that you are feeding your growing Golden Retriever the best possible diet.Royal Canin Golden Retriever Junior:Glossy coat: The combination of borage oil and biotine promotes a soft and shiny coat. Sulphureous amino acids enhance the production of keratin and support fur growth. The combination of pantothenic acid; niacin; inositol and choline strengthens skin-resistance.         A strong immune system:  An antioxidant complex strengthens the natural defences and counteracts cell ageing; while mannan-oligosaccharides stimulate immune reactions by increasing the number of antibodies. Joint protection: The synergistic effect of chondroitin sulphate and glucosamine protects the joints; supports harmonious bone development and slows down the development of arthritis. Omega-3 fatty acids EPA and DHA fight inflammations and oxidative damage. Digestive security: Rice is used as the only source of plant-based carbohydrate; while highly digestible proteins help to keep the intestinal flora balanced and healthy.   Kibble:

right_name: Taste of the Wild Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed
right_descrtiption: Royal Canin Pug Adult gives your pug exactly the right balance of nutrients for good health. If you own a pug; you know that the breed makes a happy and lively companion. These dignified; contented little dogs also show a lot of courage and dignity. Their courage means that they can find it difficult to interpret signs of aggression in other dogs and underestimate danger. Its gentle nature makes the pug the perfect dog to keep with other pets. Pugs are prone to gaining excess weight; so it is important that you feed your dog a healthy; balanced diet. Their physiology; with short jaws (brachycephalic type); gives them narrowed airways; so they often have difficulty breathing and that can have a knock-on effect on their eating habits. Feeding can be difficult; so pugs need a special kibble that is easy to eat and encourages chewing.Royal Canin Breed Pug Adult was developed with the special requirements of pugs from 10 months in mind:Maintaining ideal weight: high-quality proteins and an increased amount of L-carnitine can help dogs with a tendency to put on too many pounds to keep their ideal weightOptimal food intake: a special kibble makes feeding easier and encourages intensive chewingSkin health and coat care: fish oil; vitamin A; borage oil; chelated zinc and a special skin nutrient complex strengthen the skin's barrier function and maintain the natural beauty of the coatSlowing down the ageing process: a select complex of anti-oxidants (vitamins E and C and polyphenols) can help to protect cells against free radicalsKibble:

left_name: Taste of the Wild Southwest Canyon Adult
left_descrtiption: Taste of the Wild – Southwest Canyon combines beef; wild boar; fish and lamb to provide a high-protein unique dry food bound to be loved by every dog; no matter what breed; age or size. It is ideal for sensitive dogs as it does not use grain products; making it highly-digestible. This recipe also contains peas; which can be a vital source of vitamins; trace elements and other important nutrients. Another great source of these nutrients is the range of fruit and vegetables in this wholesome kibble; which also provide antioxidants and help maximise immune system function. The digestive system is also supported; thanks to inulin found in chicory and an ingredient called yucca schidigera. Every ingredient meets extremely high quality standards and has been designed to give your dog an enjoyable and flavourful eating experience.Taste of the Wild - Southwest Canyon dry dog food at a glance:Suitable for all dogs; no matter what age; breed or sizeA unique blend of meat proteins: A combination of delicious ingredients designed to provide your dog with health-conscious sources of energy; protein and fat.Grain-free: Many dogs struggle with digesting grains and find that they can result in adverse reactions. This food does not use any kinds of grain; making it much easier to digest and much healthier for your dog.Peas: Provide carbohydrates and other vital minerals.Perfect for sensitive dogs.A variety of sources: This unique combination of meats provides an optimum balance of amino acids; including ocean-sourced fish which gives your dog omega-3 fatty acids; great for keeping coats gleaming.Eggs: Provide highly-digestible proteins including lutein and zeaxanthin for eyesight support.Linseed: Rich in fatty acids and mucilage; for healthy coat and digestionAntioxidant-rich: For the neutralisation of free radicalsHealthy digestive system: An optimum intestinal environment is developed; thanks to chicory; yucca schidigera and inulin.Omega fatty-acids: omega-3 and -6 fatty acids can be beneficial for your dog's overall health.Raspberries and blueberries: Offer antioxidants in the form of phytonutrientsFree from: vegetable or animal by-products; waste products from slaughterhouses and additives such as flavourings.Tomatoes: For dietary fibre; lycopene and beta-carotene.All Life-Stages Nutrition: The AAFCO (Association of American Feed Control Officials) provide guidelines for the best way to meet your dog's nutritional needs at every point in its life; and this food meets those needs.Taste of the Wild – Southwest Canyon is a dry dog food ideal for all dogs; and is dog food just as nature intended.

Made with real roasted lamb this formula delivers a taste sensation.Supplemented with vegetables and fruits this hearty formula delivers antioxidants to help give your dog a healthy lifestyle.Taste of the Wild Sierra Mountain Ingredients:Lamb; lamb meal; sweet potatoes; potatoes; peas; canola oil; egg product; roasted lamb; tomato pomace; natural flavor; salmon oil (a source of DHA); salt; choline chloride; mixed tocopherols (a preservative); dried chicory root; taurine; tomatoes; blueberries; raspberries; yucca schidigera extract; dried Lactobacillus acidophilus fermentation product; dried Bifidobacterium animalis fermentation product; dried Lactobacillus reuteri fermentation product; vitamin E supplement; iron proteinate; zinc proteinate; copper proteinate; ferrous sulfate; zinc sulfate; copper sulfate; potassium iodide; thiamine mononitrate (vitamin B1); manganese proteinate; manganous oxide; ascorbic acid; vitamin A supplement; biotin; niacin; calcium pantothenate; manganese sulfate; sodium selenite; pyridoxine hydrochloride (vitamin B6); vitamin B12 supplement; riboflavin (vitamin B2); vitamin D supplement; folic acid.Protein: 25% minimumFat: 15% minimum

left_name: Taste of the Wild Pacific Stream Puppy
left_descrtiption: Taste of the Wild - Pacific Stream Puppy is a delicious grain-free delight for any breed of growing dog. This balanced recipe has been developed from the natural diets of dogs in the wild; full of everything your dog could need to live a happy and healthy lifestyle. Sweet potatoes are the carbohydrate source in this dry food; something that is much easier to digest than grains and cereals; which can lead to adverse reactions and make mealtimes an unpleasant experience for sensitive dogs. As well as being a healthy source of carbohydrate; they also provide vital vitamins such as calcium; beta-carotene and iron; and act as a source of dietary fibre. This tasty dish uses fish as its only source of protein; which adds to its already high digestibility. Salmon not only acts as a premium protein but also as a source of omega-3 fatty acids such as DHA; which are known to help with eyesight and brain development; which are naturally of the utmost importance in a growing puppy. They can also keep joints moving smoothly and coat gleaming and in tip-top condition. Inulin; yucca schidigera and chicory all work to promote healthy digestive function. Every ingredient in this food is designed to keep your dog's health at the highest possible standard; providing all necessary nutrients and even acting as a source of antioxidants to increase immune system function. A luxurious culinary delight for even the most sensitive of dogs.Taste of the Wild - Pacific Stream Puppy dry dog food at a glance:Suitable for any breed and ideal for puppies. Ideal for sensitive dogs suffering from dietary intolerance or allergic reactions to particular proteins and/or grain.Mono-source protein: By using just one source of protein; this food becomes extremely well accepted and highly-digestible.With tasty salmon: For premium protein and essential omega-3 fatty acids. Highly-digestible and delicious. Grain-free: Grain can often lead to unpleasant adverse reactions; which is why this food contains none. Grain is also high in carbohydrate; which can lead to innumerable unpleasant issues with health. By avoiding grain; this dry food provides your dog with a healthy all-round nutrition.Omega fatty acids: Omega-3 and -6 fatty acids give your dog healthy skin and glossy coat.Sweet Potatoes: Ultra nutritious and highly-digestible; they are packed full of fibre; as well as being a source of vitamins such as calcium; beta-carotene and iron.Raspberries and blueberries: Contain antioxidants in the form of phytonutrients; to help neutralise free radicals.Tomatoes: Full of vegetable fibre to promote digestion and packed with vitamins and antioxidants; including lycopene and beta-carotene.Free from: Animal and vegetable by-products; waste products from the slaughterhouse and artificial flavourings and colourings. All Life-Stages Nutrition: Taste of the Wild dog food has been designed to continue meeting your dog's needs at every point in its life; according to the AAFCO (Association of American Feed Control Officials) recommendations.Taste of the Wild – Pacific Stream Puppy dog food is ideal for junior dogs and puppies of any breed - dog food just as nature intended.

right_descrtiption: Royal Canin Mini Dermacomfort is a unique food that can help small dogs that suffer from skin irritation. Healthy skin is vital to ensuring your dog’s wellbeing; as it forms a barrier which protects the organs; and prevents the body from drying out. It also protects the body from injury and infections from harmful bacteria; as well as storing fats and vitamins and being an important source of sensory information.Itching; dandruff; a greasy coat or dry skin are all signs that something may be wrong with your dog. These complaints can affect your dog’s overall wellbeing; so they should not be ignored. Royal Canin Mini Dermacomfort has a combination of active ingredients designed to combat skin complaints and improve the skin’s health. Royal Canin Mini Dermacomfort dog food contains a unique combination of nutrients and a patented complex to improve and keep your dog’s fur and skin healthy. After only one month of feeding your dog Royal Canin Dermacomfort you will notice an improvement; with less scratching and itching.Royal Canin Health Nutrition - know and respect your dog's behavioural and nutritional requirements to ensure its wellbeing and health. Visible results achieved after only one month of feedingLess scratching and itching

left_descrtiption: For dogs that show signs of being sensitive to some of the ingredients used in traditional pet foods; less may be more. BLUE Basics contains:  Turkey - A high-quality protein not typically used in dog food. Oatmeal; Potatoes and Brown Rice - Three easily digestible carbohydrate sources. A Precise Blend of Veggies; Fruit and Micronutrients - Selected for their nutritional value; and their capacity to help in the digestive process. An Optimal Blend of Omega 3 and 6 Fatty Acids - Helps maintain the immune system to help support skin and coat health.  For dogs with food sensitivities; the ingredients they don't eat can be just as important as the ones they do. BLUE Basics contains:  NO corn NO wheat NO dairy NO soy NO eggs  And; like all BLUE pet foods; BLUE Basics contains no chicken or poultry by-product meals and no artificial ingredients of any kind.

right_descrtiption: Royal Canin German Shepherd Junior dry dog food has been specially developed to meet the individual nutritional needs of your growing dog. As they age; young German Shepherds go through an important growth phase; which must be kept at a stable rate to help prevent later health problems. This complete dry food is intended to promote balanced growth in junior German Shepherds up to 15 months old. Alongside maintaining a steady growth rate; Royal Canin Breed German Shepherd Junior helps to promote your dog's intestinal health and boost their natural defences. Your growing dog will also benefit from additional skin and coat protection thanks to the careful blend of vitamins and amino acids.  German Shepherds have a truly noble character that makes them popular both as a working dog and as a domestic companion. They are also incredibly strong and handsome dogs; boasting powerful muscles and a well-developed chest. Royal Canin Junior German Shepherd bears all of these breed characteristics in mind; guaranteeing a dry dog food that meets all of your dog's nutritional requirements. Royal Canin German Shepherd Junior:Optimal digestive security: Rice as a single source of plant carbohydrates; high-grade L.I.P. proteins (>90%) and soya bean oil all contribute to a healthy digestive system. Select; special fibres limit the fermentation process in the digestive tract; while maintaining the balance of the intestinal flora.Strengthening the immune system and reducing oxidative stress: An antioxidant complex contributes to the strengthening of the immune system and slows cell ageing. Mannan-oligosaccharides stimulate a response from the immune system; which raises the quantity of antibodies (immunoglobulin A; white blood cells).  Skin protection and radiant fur: Royal Canin Breed German Shepherd Junior dog food strengthens the barrier function of the skin and maintains the natural shine of your dog's fur with a mixture of vitamins and amino acids.Joint protection and balanced growth: The synergistic effect of chrondroitin sulphate and glucosamines protects the joints and helps to slow the development of arthritis; inflammation and oxidative damage with the help of omega-3 fatty acids EPA and DHAKibble:

left_name: Royal Canin Dachshund Adult
left_descrtiption: The Dachshund; also known as sausage dog; is a spirited dog and an excellent hunter. The dachshund owes his popularity on all five continents to his characteristic silhouette with short; bent limbs (chondrodystrophic type). Since time immemorial this form has been considered a great hunting advantage; because it allows the dachshund to follow rabbits and badgers right into their den. However this causes the Dachshund to have especially sensitive joints.Dachshunds have a one of longest life expectancies of any dog. However; the restful lifestyle of your dachshund can accelerate oxidative stress and the related cell ageing process that follows. It is important that the nutrition of your Dachshund limits the effect of oxidative stress and ensures healthy digestion for as long as possible.Dachshunds often have a natural tendency to become overweight. Obesity can overburden your pet's sensitive back bone; which can lead to grave consequences.Royal CaninBreed Dachshund Dog Food was specially developed with aforementioned characteristics in mind.Joint Protection:Royal Canin Breed Dachshund Dog Food helps protect your loved one's joints due to its chondroitin and glucoasmine as well as a high component of EPA/DHA fatty acids. The same ingredients also ensure proper care for your dog's cartilageMuscle Strain and Ideal Weight Maintenance: a high protein content as well as the addition of conjugated linoleic acid (CLA) and L-Carnitin mobilize body fatDeceleration of the Ageing Process: an anti-oxidant complex (vitamin E and C; polyphenole) can protect the cells from free radicals and well being late in your pet's lifeReduced Stool Odour and Healthy Digestion:  highly digestible nutrients and the integration of FOS (Fructo-Oligosaccharide) ensure healthy; regular digestionDental Hygiene:  a tailored kibble form and structure encourage proper mechanical teeth cleaning. Calcium chelate significantly reduces tartar formation.Kibble:

Each recipe is made with real roasted meats and supplemented with vegetables; legumes and fruits. These grain free recipes provide a superior taste sensation; highly digestible energy and antioxidants to support a healthy immune system. left_name: Royal Canin Beagle Adult
left_descrtiption: Beagles are happy and inquisitive pets. They are bold; very active dogs with lots of energy; stamina and determination. They are even-tempered and intelligent and their amiable character makes them a great family pet. Beagles are by nature pack dogs and have a tendency to overeat and to put on weight. Royal Canin Beagle is a complete dry food which has a texture and composition to suit the specific nutritional needs of your dog. It provides your beagle with a balanced nutrition and all the nutrients it needs to stay healthy. The kibble has a texture and shape that is suitable for the way beagles eat. The exclusive shape helps reduce the rate of food intake and encourages chewing. This formula also contains a combination of fibres. Your dog will eat more slowly and feel fuller more quickly; and the chewing will aid dental hygiene.Royal Canin Beagle also contains ingredients which help to support healthy bones and joints as well as helping your dog to maintain its ideal weight.Royal Canin Beagle at a glance:Specially shaped and textured kibble to encourage slower feeding and good dental hygieneModerate fat content to help your dog maintain its ideal weightFormulated to support bones and jointsBreed specific formula to ensure a balanced and healthy dietRich with EPA & DHA

left_name: Royal Canin Pug Adult
left_descrtiption: Royal Canin Pug Adult gives your pug exactly the right balance of nutrients for good health. If you own a pug; you know that the breed makes a happy and lively companion. These dignified; contented little dogs also show a lot of courage and dignity. Their courage means that they can find it difficult to interpret signs of aggression in other dogs and underestimate danger. Its gentle nature makes the pug the perfect dog to keep with other pets. Pugs are prone to gaining excess weight; so it is important that you feed your dog a healthy; balanced diet. Their physiology; with short jaws (brachycephalic type); gives them narrowed airways; so they often have difficulty breathing and that can have a knock-on effect on their eating habits. Feeding can be difficult; so pugs need a special kibble that is easy to eat and encourages chewing.Royal Canin Breed Pug Adult was developed with the special requirements of pugs from 10 months in mind:Maintaining ideal weight: high-quality proteins and an increased amount of L-carnitine can help dogs with a tendency to put on too many pounds to keep their ideal weightOptimal food intake: a special kibble makes feeding easier and encourages intensive chewingSkin health and coat care: fish oil; vitamin A; borage oil; chelated zinc and a special skin nutrient complex strengthen the skin's barrier function and maintain the natural beauty of the coatSlowing down the ageing process: a select complex of anti-oxidants (vitamins E and C and polyphenols) can help to protect cells against free radicalsKibble:

left_name: Royal Canin Yorkshire Terrier Adult 7.5kg
left_descrtiption: Royal Canin Yorkshire Terrier 28 Adult 7.5kgYorkshire 28 Breed specific product; especially for the Yorkshire Terrier from 10 months of age. Disigned to take account of all the special characteristics of the breed.COAT HEALTHThis exclusive formula contributes to maintaining health of the Yorkshire’s long coat. Enriched with adapted content of Omega 3 fatty acids (EPA & DHA); Omega 6 fatty acids; borage oil and biotin.SATISFIES FUSSY APPETITESThis formula satisfies the fussiest of appetites thanks to a combination of exceptional flavours.HEALTHY AGEING SUPPORTThis formula supplies a selection of nutrients to help maintain health in mature dogs.EXCLUSIVE KIBBLE: DENTAL HEALTHThis formula helps reduce tartar formation thanks to calcium chelators.IngredientsCOMPOSITION: dehydrated poultry protein; maize flour; rice; animal fats; vegetable protein isolate*;maize; maize gluten; hydrolysed animal proteins; vegetable fibres; beet pulp; minerals; fish oil; yeasts; soya oil; fructo-oligo- saccharides; hydrolysed yeast(source of manno-oligo-saccharides); borage oil (0.1%); green tea and grape extracts(source of polyphenols); marigold extract (source of lutein); hydrolysed crustaceans (source of glucosamine); hydrolysed cartilage (source of chondroitin). ADDITIVES (per kg): Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 29500 IU; Vitamin D3: 800 IU; Biotin: 3.07 mg; E1 (Iron): 47 mg; E2 (Iodine): 4.7 mg; E4 (Copper): 9 mg; E5 (Manganese): 61 mg; E6 (Zinc):183 mg; E8 (Selenium): 0.1 mg - Technological additives:Pentasodium triphosphate: 3.5 g - Preservatives - Antioxidants. ANALYTICAL CONSTITUENTS: Protein: 28% - Fat content: 18% - Crude ash: 5% - Crude fibres: 3.1% - Per kg: Omega 3 fatty acids:6.8 g including EPA & DHA: 3 g - Omega 6 fatty acids: 33.7 g. *L.I.P.: protein selected for its very high assimilation.

left_name: Royal Canin Great Dane Adult 12kg
left_descrtiption: Great Dane Adult 24 Months +  - Complete dog feed for adult and mature Great Danes - Over 24 months oldGreat Dane 23. Breed specific product; especially for the Great Dane from 18 months of age. Disigned to take account of all the special characteristics of the breed.CONCENTRATED ENERGYAdequate energy level to meet the high needs of Great Danes without overloading the stomach. It is important to divide the daily ration into at least 2 meals in order to limit the risk of gastric dilatation-volvulus.DIGESTIVE PERFORMANCEContributes to supporting digestive health while taking into account the Great Dane’s digestive sensitivity; thanks to highly digestible L.I.P. proteins and a selection of specific fibres to limit intestinal fermentation while promoting a balance in the intestinal flora.BONE & JOINT HEALTHThis specific formula helps support healthy bones and joints and maintain ideal weight. ADDITIVES (per kg): Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 31200 IU; Vitamin D3: 800 IU; E1 (Iron): 51 mg; E2 (Iodine): 5.1 mg; E4 (Copper): 6 mg; E5 (Manganese): 66 mg; E6 (Zinc): 199 mg; E8 (Selenium): 0.11 mg - Preservatives - Antioxidants. right_descrtiption: Taste of the Wild Sierra Mountain Adult has based itself on the natural canine diet adapted to meet the modern dog’s needs and habits. It is a complete dry dog food ideal for any breed; age or size of dog and is entirely species-appropriate. Lamb acts as the sole animal protein source in this Taste of the Wild Sierra Mountain Adult; full of wholesome flavour as well as having a low allergenic potential; making it ideal even for sensitive dogs. This dish is grain-free; using flavoursome sweet potato as a source of carbohydrate and fibre. This vegetable is also a great source of valuable vitamins and nutrients; including calcium; beta-carotene and iron. Taste of the Wild Sierra Mountain Adult is also a vital provider of antioxidants; renowned for their free radical neutralising properties and a key asset in immune system strength. Chicory acts a source of natural prebiotic inulin; while yucca schidigera has been added to keep the digestion functioning smoothly and stool odours to a minimum. Each ingredient that goes into this premium Taste of the Wild food is of the finest quality; making it a highly digestible and enjoyable dish for even the most sensitive of dogs.Taste of the Wild Sierra Mountain Adult at a glance:Lamb: Roasted lamb has a hearty taste and provides premium protein with low allergenic potentialEggs: With premium; easy to digest proteins such as lutein and zeaxanthin which help to protect the eyesight Sweet Potatoes: Sweet potatoes are a nourishing; easy to digest source of energy. They easy to digest; full of important fibre and rich in vitamins; iron; calcium and beta-carotene.Tomatoes: A natural source of vegetable fibre for a healthy digestive system and with healthy vitamins and powerful antioxidants such as beta-carotene and lycopene. Blueberries and Raspberries: These berries are packed with phytonutrients full of antioxidants to help keep the cells healthySingle protein: Only one source of animal protein to ensure high acceptabilityGrain-free: This kibble provides a balanced nutrition to keep your dog healthy and vital. Many vets believe that grain in pet food is the cause of many health problems. The high carbohydrate content in grain can lead to obesity; diabetes; digestion problems and other illnessesHealthy digestive system: Dried chicory root and Yucca Schidigera provide prebiotic inulin which supports a healthy intestinal flora and immune systemRich in antioxidants: To protect the cells from free radicals and to help keep the immune system working wellOmega fatty acids: - Omega-6 and Omega-3 fatty acids work to together to help maintain healthy skin and a shiny coat as well as overall good health.For dogs of all ages; breeds and sizeAll Life-Stages Nutrition: Taste of the Wild dog food is formulated to meet the recommended nutrient profiles of AAFCO (Association of American Feed Control Officials) and fulfils the nutritional needs of your pet throughout all stages of life.Suitable for dogs which suffer with food intolerances and allergies to grain or certain proteinsNO: Slaughterhouse waste; vegetable or animal by-products; taste enhancers; attractants Taste of the Wild Sierra Mountain Adult offers a canine diet as close to nature as possible; ideal for dogs of any size or breed.

right_descrtiption: Royal Canin Labrador Retriever offers a wide range of benefits and is an excellent quality food for your dog.Ideal weight formulaHelps maintain the Labrador's ideal weight with increased protein and lower fat plus L-carnitine.An exclusive kibble shape and formula help promote a feeling of fullness.Support for strong bone structureHelps provide support for the Labrador's strong bone structure.Beautiful and healthy waterproof coatReveals the beauty of the Labrador's unique waterproof coat and helps maintain the barrier role of their skin.Vision supportSupports the eyes antioxidant defencesRoyal Canin Labrador Retriever Ingredients:dehydrated poultry protein; rice; wheat; maize; maize gluten; animal fats; vegetable protein isolate*; hydrolysed animal proteins; vegetable fibres; beet pulp; yeasts; fish oil; minerals; soya oil; fructo-oligo-saccharides; psyllium husks and seeds; hydrolysed crustaceans (source of glucosamine); borage oil (0.1%); green tea extracts (source of polyphenols); marigold extract (source of lutein); hydrolysed cartilage (source of chondroitin).Analysis:Protein: 30%; Fat content: 13%; Crude ash: 6.6%; Crude fibres: 3.8%; EPA and DHA fatty acids: 4 g/kg.

left_name: Royal Canin Labrador Retriever Adult
left_descrtiption: Royal Canin Labrador Retriever Adult is a tasty; dry dog food; which offers a complete and balanced meal. Specially formulated to avoid your Labrador from overeating and gaining excessive weight; this kibble also helps to ensure your dog’s joints are supported. Feeding your Labrador Retriever Royal Canin will really help them develop; as they are being given a delicious meal which is rich in all the nutrients they need to thrive. Labrador Retrievers are well-known as an energetic and lively breed of dog – they just love going on walkies! However; their active nature leads to more wear-and-tear on their joints and cartilage; which can later cause arthritis. Royal Canin Labrador dry food is enriched with minerals to help maintain your dog’s healthy joints.Labradors tend to have a rather low calorie requirement; but they often gain weight by over-feeding. Royal Canin Labrador Retriever Adult is also the perfect food for helping your dog to maintain a healthy weight; due to the adapted calorie content.Royal Canin Labrador Retriever Adult kibble is suitable for Labrador Retrievers aged 15+ months and weighing 26-40kg.Royal Canin Labrador Retriever Adult dry dog food:Ideal weight: Reduced fat content (13%) and L-carnitine for stimulating the digestion of fats helps contribute towards maintaining you Labrador Retriever’s ideal weight.  A special kibble thickness and shape as well as a recipe containing barley and psyllium help to provide a quick feeling a satisfaction and fullness.Strengthening the joints: Royal Canin Labrador Retriever dog food helps to strengthen joints and thus can help provide stronger support for your Labrador’s bones.  The joint nutrients chondroitin-sulphate and glucosamine slow down the wearing of the joints and stimulate joint cell regeneration.  The omega 3 fatty acids EPA and DHA work to reduce inflammation and manganese and a complex of anti-oxidants protect from oxidative damage.Skin protection and radiant fur: Royal Canin Breed Labrador Retriever Dog Food strengthens the barrier function of the skin and maintains the natural shine of your dog's fur thanks to a mixture of vitamins and amino acids.Natural Eyesight Maintenance: An anti-oxidant complex (lutein; Zeaxanthin; vitamins E & C) helps maintain eyesight.Kibble:

left_name: Natural Balance LID Fish Small Breed Dry Dog Food
left_descrtiption: Natural Balance® L.I.D. Limited Ingredient Diets® Sweet Potato & Small Breed Bites® Fish Dry Dog FoodNatural Balance® L.I.D. Limited Ingredient Diets® Sweet Potato & Fish Small Breed Bites® is complete and balanced nutrition for small breed dogs of all life stages. High-quality fish provides an excellent source of protein; while sweet potatoes provide carbohydrates; essential for energy. The kibble is also a special size; shape and texture; which helps to promote clean teeth and healthy gums. Every bite is packed with flavor; rich in nutrients; and easy to digest. Balanced Omega 3 and 6 fatty acids help support healthy skin and a shiny coat.Features:Complete; balanced nutrition for adult maintenanceFormulated to provide high-quality nutrition for all breedsEncourages digestive healthSpecially designed to help support clean teeth and healthy gums for small breed dogsPremium grain-free energy sourceSupports healthy skin and shiny coatNo artificial flavors or colors Item Specifications:Flavor:Sweet Potato & FishGuaranteed Analysis:Crude Protein (min.): 21.0%Crude Fat (min.): 10.0%Crude Fiber (max.): 5.0%Moisture (max.): 10.0%Docosahexaenoic Acid (DHA)* (min.): 0.05%Calcium (min.): 0.6%Phosphorus (min.): 0.5%Omega 6 Fatty Acids* (min.): 1.1%Omega 3 Fatty Acids* (min.): 0.5%Calorie Content (Calculated): ME = 3340 kcal/kg; 350 kcal/cup*Not recognized as an essential nutrient by the AAFCO Dog Food Nutrient Profiles.Ingredients:Sweet Potatoes; Salmon; Menhaden Fish Meal; Potato Protein; Canola Oil (Preserved with Mixed Tocopherols); Natural Flavor; Dried Potato Products; Salt; Salmon Oil (Preserved With Mixed Tocopherols); Dl-Methionine; Minerals (Zinc Proteinate; Zinc Sulfate; Ferrous Sulfate; Iron Proteinate; Copper Sulfate; Copper Proteinate; Manganese Sulfate; Manganese Proteinate; Calcium Iodate; Sodium Selenite); Vitamins (Vitamin E Supplement; Niacin; D-Calcium Pantothenate; Vitamin A Supplement; Riboflavin Supplement; Thiamine Mononitrate; Vitamin D3 Supplement; Pyridoxine Hydrochloride; Folic Acid; Biotin; Vitamin B12 Supplement); Choline Chloride; Flaxseed; Potassium Chloride; Taurine; Citric Acid (Preservative); Mixed Tocopherols (Preservative); Rosemary Extract.Daily Feeding Guidelines:10 lb. or less: up to 1 cup 10-20 lb.: 1 - 1½ cups 20-30 lb.: 1½ - 2¼ cups30-40 lb.: 2¼ - 2¾ cupsThese amounts are intended as guidelines only. The food intake should be adjusted according to the age; weight; breed; temperature; climate and activity level of your dog. Consult a veterinarian for specific weight recommendations.Feeding Management:Do not add vitamins; minerals; or any other supplements; except upon the advice of a veterinarian. When switching your dog's diet; the change should be made gradually by replacing the current food with increasing portions of Natural Balance® L.I.D. Limited Ingredient Diets® Sweet Potato & Fish Small Breed Bites® Dry Dog Formula. The change should be completed after 5 to 7 days. The maintenance of proper body weight is most important for your dog's health. Consult your veterinarian for specific weight recommendations for your dog. Fresh clean water should be available at all times.

Royal Canin Labrador Retriever Adult is also the perfect food for helping your dog to maintain a healthy weight; due to the adapted calorie content.Royal Canin Labrador Retriever Adult kibble is suitable for Labrador Retrievers aged 15+ months and weighing 26-40kg.Royal Canin Labrador Retriever Adult dry dog food:Ideal weight: Reduced fat content (13%) and L-carnitine for stimulating the digestion of fats helps contribute towards maintaining you Labrador Retriever’s ideal weight.  A special kibble thickness and shape as well as a recipe containing barley and psyllium help to provide a quick feeling a satisfaction and fullness.Strengthening the joints: Royal Canin Labrador Retriever dog food helps to strengthen joints and thus can help provide stronger support for your Labrador’s bones.  The joint nutrients chondroitin-sulphate and glucosamine slow down the wearing of the joints and stimulate joint cell regeneration.  The omega 3 fatty acids EPA and DHA work to reduce inflammation and manganese and a complex of anti-oxidants protect from oxidative damage.Skin protection and radiant fur: Royal Canin Breed Labrador Retriever Dog Food strengthens the barrier function of the skin and maintains the natural shine of your dog's fur thanks to a mixture of vitamins and amino acids.Natural Eyesight Maintenance: An anti-oxidant complex (lutein; Zeaxanthin; vitamins E & C) helps maintain eyesight.Kibble:

left_name: Royal Canin Beagle Adult 12kg
left_descrtiption: Royal Canin Beagle Adult 12kgBeagle Adult 12 months + Complete feed for dogs - Specially for adult and mature Beagles - Over 12 months old. Benefits include IdealWeight Formula; Exclusively Kibble; Bone and Joint Support; Food intake control;IDEAL WEIGHTThe Beagle is known for his tendency to gain weight. This formula helps maintain the Beagle’s ideal weight thanks to an adapted calorie content.FOOD INTAKE CONTROLThe kibble’s exclusive shape helps reduce the rate of food intake and encourage chewing. This formula also contains a combination of fibres.BONE AND JOINT HEALTHThis specific formula helps support healthy bones and joints and maintain ideal weight. ADDITIVES (per kg): Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 28000 IU; Vitamin D3: 700 IU; E1 (Iron): 42 mg; E2 (Iodine): 4.2 mg; E4 (Copper): 5 mg; E5 (Manganese): 55 mg; E6 (Zinc): 164 mg; E8(Selenium): 0.09 mg - Preservatives - Antioxidants. left_name: Royal Canin German Shepherd Junior
left_descrtiption: Royal Canin German Shepherd Junior dry dog food has been specially developed to meet the individual nutritional needs of your growing dog. As they age; young German Shepherds go through an important growth phase; which must be kept at a stable rate to help prevent later health problems. This complete dry food is intended to promote balanced growth in junior German Shepherds up to 15 months old. Alongside maintaining a steady growth rate; Royal Canin Breed German Shepherd Junior helps to promote your dog's intestinal health and boost their natural defences. Your growing dog will also benefit from additional skin and coat protection thanks to the careful blend of vitamins and amino acids.  German Shepherds have a truly noble character that makes them popular both as a working dog and as a domestic companion. They are also incredibly strong and handsome dogs; boasting powerful muscles and a well-developed chest. Royal Canin Junior German Shepherd bears all of these breed characteristics in mind; guaranteeing a dry dog food that meets all of your dog's nutritional requirements. Royal Canin German Shepherd Junior:Optimal digestive security: Rice as a single source of plant carbohydrates; high-grade L.I.P. proteins (>90%) and soya bean oil all contribute to a healthy digestive system. Select; special fibres limit the fermentation process in the digestive tract; while maintaining the balance of the intestinal flora.Strengthening the immune system and reducing oxidative stress: An antioxidant complex contributes to the strengthening of the immune system and slows cell ageing. Mannan-oligosaccharides stimulate a response from the immune system; which raises the quantity of antibodies (immunoglobulin A; white blood cells).  Skin protection and radiant fur: Royal Canin Breed German Shepherd Junior dog food strengthens the barrier function of the skin and maintains the natural shine of your dog's fur with a mixture of vitamins and amino acids.Joint protection and balanced growth: The synergistic effect of chrondroitin sulphate and glucosamines protects the joints and helps to slow the development of arthritis; inflammation and oxidative damage with the help of omega-3 fatty acids EPA and DHAKibble:

left_name: Taste of the Wild Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed
left_descrtiption: Taste of the Wild - Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed is a balanced dry food for small breeds of dog of all ages. This biologically-appropriate diet is based on the original feeding habits of your dog and is rich in venison; lamb and duck. Dogs love the hearty taste of lean meat and they can easily digest this form of high-quality protein. Taste of the Wild - Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed is completely grain and gluten free; so this tasty dry food can be fed to dogs with nutritional intolerances and allergies. Protein-rich pulses; such as chickpeas and lentils; provide the easy-to-digest; necessary carbohydrates. This dry food has an extra-small kibble size; which is suited to small jaws and makes chewing easier.Taste of the Wild - Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed also contains a balanced mix of fruits; vegetables and plant fibres; which are rich in essential vitamins and minerals. Chicory with the prebiotic inulin and Yucca Schidigera help to promote your dog’s wellbeing and a healthy digestive system; while the high antioxidant content helps to strengthen the immune system and protect the body’s cells against free radicals. Omega fatty acids help to keep your dog’s coat glossy and skin healthy. Water used in the cooking process is purified by reverse osmosis; which guarantees safe; sterile water. This biologically-appropriate diet is based on the original feeding habits of your dog and is rich in venison; lamb and duck. Dogs love the hearty taste of lean meat and they can easily digest this form of high-quality protein. Taste of the Wild - Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed is completely grain and gluten free; so this tasty dry food can be fed to dogs with nutritional intolerances and allergies. Protein-rich pulses; such as chickpeas and lentils; provide the easy-to-digest; necessary carbohydrates. This dry food has an extra-small kibble size; which is suited to small jaws and makes chewing easier.Taste of the Wild - Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed also contains a balanced mix of fruits; vegetables and plant fibres; which are rich in essential vitamins and minerals. Chicory with the prebiotic inulin and Yucca Schidigera help to promote your dog’s wellbeing and a healthy digestive system; while the high antioxidant content helps to strengthen the immune system and protect the body’s cells against free radicals. Omega fatty acids help to keep your dog’s coat glossy and skin healthy. Water used in the cooking process is purified by reverse osmosis; which guarantees safe; sterile water.  Taste of the Wild - Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed:Premium dry food for small breeds of dog of all ages Small kibble size: specifically suited to small jaws; making it easier to chewGluten and grain free: grain-free dog foods are very well accepted and are perfect for dogs with nutritional allergies or intolerancesVenison; lamb and duck: plenty of lean; delicious meat provides your dog with high-quality; easy-to-digest protein and sufficient energy to keep them in great shape Optimal amino acid profile: a balanced mix of animal proteins; egg; chickpeas; lentils and other pulses ensures an optimal amino acid profile; which is necessary to maintain your dog’s healthRich in antioxidants: promote a healthy immune system and help to protect cells from free radicals Healthy digestive system: dried chicory root and Yucca Schidigera extract provide prebiotic inulin; which supports healthy intestinal flora and the immune systemOmega fatty acids: omega-6 and omega-3 fatty acids promote a glossy coat and healthy skinBlueberries and raspberries: these berries are rich in phytonutrients; which have antioxidant properties to protect cellsTomatoes: a natural source of vegetable fibre for a healthy digestive system and with healthy vitamins and powerful antioxidants such as beta-carotene and lycopene Eggs: a source of premium; easy-to-digest proteins such as lutein and zeaxanthin; which help to protect your dog’s eyesightPurified water: water used in the cooking process is purified by reverse osmosis; which guarantees safe; sterile water that has any inorganic chemicals removedNO: slaughterhouse waste; vegetable or animal by-products; taste enhancers; attractantsAll Life-Stages Nutrition: Taste of the Wild dog food is formulated to meet the recommended nutrient profiles of AAFCO (Association of American Feed Control Officials) and fulfils the nutritional needs of your pet throughout all stages of life.

left_name: Taste of the Wild Pacific Stream Puppy
left_descrtiption: Taste of the Wild - Pacific Stream Puppy is a delicious grain-free delight for any breed of growing dog. This balanced recipe has been developed from the natural diets of dogs in the wild; full of everything your dog could need to live a happy and healthy lifestyle. Sweet potatoes are the carbohydrate source in this dry food; something that is much easier to digest than grains and cereals; which can lead to adverse reactions and make mealtimes an unpleasant experience for sensitive dogs. As well as being a healthy source of carbohydrate; they also provide vital vitamins such as calcium; beta-carotene and iron; and act as a source of dietary fibre. This tasty dish uses fish as its only source of protein; which adds to its already high digestibility. Salmon not only acts as a premium protein but also as a source of omega-3 fatty acids such as DHA; which are known to help with eyesight and brain development; which are naturally of the utmost importance in a growing puppy. They can also keep joints moving smoothly and coat gleaming and in tip-top condition. Inulin; yucca schidigera and chicory all work to promote healthy digestive function. Every ingredient in this food is designed to keep your dog's health at the highest possible standard; providing all necessary nutrients and even acting as a source of antioxidants to increase immune system function. A luxurious culinary delight for even the most sensitive of dogs.Taste of the Wild - Pacific Stream Puppy dry dog food at a glance:Suitable for any breed and ideal for puppies. Ideal for sensitive dogs suffering from dietary intolerance or allergic reactions to particular proteins and/or grain.Mono-source protein: By using just one source of protein; this food becomes extremely well accepted and highly-digestible.With tasty salmon: For premium protein and essential omega-3 fatty acids. Highly-digestible and delicious. Grain-free: Grain can often lead to unpleasant adverse reactions; which is why this food contains none. Grain is also high in carbohydrate; which can lead to innumerable unpleasant issues with health. By avoiding grain; this dry food provides your dog with a healthy all-round nutrition.Omega fatty acids: Omega-3 and -6 fatty acids give your dog healthy skin and glossy coat.Sweet Potatoes: Ultra nutritious and highly-digestible; they are packed full of fibre; as well as being a source of vitamins such as calcium; beta-carotene and iron.Raspberries and blueberries: Contain antioxidants in the form of phytonutrients; to help neutralise free radicals.Tomatoes: Full of vegetable fibre to promote digestion and packed with vitamins and antioxidants; including lycopene and beta-carotene.Free from: Animal and vegetable by-products; waste products from the slaughterhouse and artificial flavourings and colourings. All Life-Stages Nutrition: Taste of the Wild dog food has been designed to continue meeting your dog's needs at every point in its life; according to the AAFCO (Association of American Feed Control Officials) recommendations.Taste of the Wild – Pacific Stream Puppy dog food is ideal for junior dogs and puppies of any breed - dog food just as nature intended.

right_name: Taste of the Wild Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed
right_descrtiption: Royal Canin German Shepherd Junior dry dog food has been specially developed to meet the individual nutritional needs of your growing dog. As they age; young German Shepherds go through an important growth phase; which must be kept at a stable rate to help prevent later health problems. This complete dry food is intended to promote balanced growth in junior German Shepherds up to 15 months old. Alongside maintaining a steady growth rate; Royal Canin Breed German Shepherd Junior helps to promote your dog's intestinal health and boost their natural defences. Your growing dog will also benefit from additional skin and coat protection thanks to the careful blend of vitamins and amino acids.  German Shepherds have a truly noble character that makes them popular both as a working dog and as a domestic companion. They are also incredibly strong and handsome dogs; boasting powerful muscles and a well-developed chest. Royal Canin Junior German Shepherd bears all of these breed characteristics in mind; guaranteeing a dry dog food that meets all of your dog's nutritional requirements. Royal Canin German Shepherd Junior:Optimal digestive security: Rice as a single source of plant carbohydrates; high-grade L.I.P. proteins (>90%) and soya bean oil all contribute to a healthy digestive system. Select; special fibres limit the fermentation process in the digestive tract; while maintaining the balance of the intestinal flora.Strengthening the immune system and reducing oxidative stress: An antioxidant complex contributes to the strengthening of the immune system and slows cell ageing. Mannan-oligosaccharides stimulate a response from the immune system; which raises the quantity of antibodies (immunoglobulin A; white blood cells).  Skin protection and radiant fur: Royal Canin Breed German Shepherd Junior dog food strengthens the barrier function of the skin and maintains the natural shine of your dog's fur with a mixture of vitamins and amino acids.Joint protection and balanced growth: The synergistic effect of chrondroitin sulphate and glucosamines protects the joints and helps to slow the development of arthritis; inflammation and oxidative damage with the help of omega-3 fatty acids EPA and DHAKibble:

This biologically-appropriate diet is based on the original feeding habits of your dog and is rich in venison; lamb and duck. Dogs love the hearty taste of lean meat and they can easily digest this form of high-quality protein. Taste of the Wild - Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed is completely grain and gluten free; so this tasty dry food can be fed to dogs with nutritional intolerances and allergies. Protein-rich pulses; such as chickpeas and lentils; provide the easy-to-digest; necessary carbohydrates. This dry food has an extra-small kibble size; which is suited to small jaws and makes chewing easier.Taste of the Wild - Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed also contains a balanced mix of fruits; vegetables and plant fibres; which are rich in essential vitamins and minerals. Chicory with the prebiotic inulin and Yucca Schidigera help to promote your dog’s wellbeing and a healthy digestive system; while the high antioxidant content helps to strengthen the immune system and protect the body’s cells against free radicals. Omega fatty acids help to keep your dog’s coat glossy and skin healthy. Water used in the cooking process is purified by reverse osmosis; which guarantees safe; sterile water.  Taste of the Wild - Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed:Premium dry food for small breeds of dog of all ages Small kibble size: specifically suited to small jaws; making it easier to chewGluten and grain free: grain-free dog foods are very well accepted and are perfect for dogs with nutritional allergies or intolerancesVenison; lamb and duck: plenty of lean; delicious meat provides your dog with high-quality; easy-to-digest protein and sufficient energy to keep them in great shape Optimal amino acid profile: a balanced mix of animal proteins; egg; chickpeas; lentils and other pulses ensures an optimal amino acid profile; which is necessary to maintain your dog’s healthRich in antioxidants: promote a healthy immune system and help to protect cells from free radicals Healthy digestive system: dried chicory root and Yucca Schidigera extract provide prebiotic inulin; which supports healthy intestinal flora and the immune systemOmega fatty acids: omega-6 and omega-3 fatty acids promote a glossy coat and healthy skinBlueberries and raspberries: these berries are rich in phytonutrients; which have antioxidant properties to protect cellsTomatoes: a natural source of vegetable fibre for a healthy digestive system and with healthy vitamins and powerful antioxidants such as beta-carotene and lycopene Eggs: a source of premium; easy-to-digest proteins such as lutein and zeaxanthin; which help to protect your dog’s eyesightPurified water: water used in the cooking process is purified by reverse osmosis; which guarantees safe; sterile water that has any inorganic chemicals removedNO: slaughterhouse waste; vegetable or animal by-products; taste enhancers; attractantsAll Life-Stages Nutrition: Taste of the Wild dog food is formulated to meet the recommended nutrient profiles of AAFCO (Association of American Feed Control Officials) and fulfils the nutritional needs of your pet throughout all stages of life.
right_name: Taste of the Wild Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed
right_descrtiption: Puppies need balanced and adapted nutrition for healthy development. Royal Canin Labrador Retriever Junior is a complete dry kibble that has been especially formulated to meet the needs of growing Labrador puppies up to 15 months of age. This food will see them through the crucial growing phase; ensuring healthy development. This balanced dry kibble contains added prebiotics; which can help to support a good balance of intestinal flora. Prebiotics have also been shown to be decisive in building a strong immune system.Even though your puppy may be very energetic and have a huge appetite; he only needs a relatively moderate calorie intake per day. Labrador Retriever Junior has a moderate energy content and; if fed correctly; should help your puppy to grow whilst also maintaining a healthy weight.Although your dog is naturally active; his joints can come under a lot of stress; with a high risk of developing arthritis. Labrador Retriever Junior contains chondroitin and glucosamine to protect and support good joint health into adulthood.Royal Canin Labrador Retriever Junior: Balanced growth: an optimal amount of protein and balanced supplies of calcium and phosphorus support harmonious bone developmentIdeal weight: Reduced fat content (14%) and L-carnitine for stimulating the digestion of fats helps contribute towards maintaining you Labrador Retriever’s ideal weight.  A special kibble thickness and shape as well as a recipe containing barley and psyllium help to provide a quick feeling a satisfaction and fullness.Strengthening the joints: Royal Canin Breed Labrador Retriever Junior dog food helps to strengthen joints and can help provide stronger support for your Labrador’s bones.  The joint nutrients chondroitin and glucosamine slow down the wearing of the joints and stimulate joint cell regeneration.  The omega 3 fatty acids EPA and DHA work to reduce inflammation and manganese and a complex of anti-oxidants protect from oxidative damageStrong immune system: the special anti-oxidant complex helps to strengthen the natural defences and develop a strong; natural immune systemHigh digestibility: pre-biotics and psyllium support a balanced intestinal flora

left_name: Royal Canin Labrador retriever junior 12Kg
left_descrtiption: Royal Canin Labrador Junior is especially formulated for optimum growth management. Ensures the consolidation of the bone structure.Helps strengthen the barrier role of the skin and promotes a glossy coat. For dogs aged 5-15 months.Royal Canin Labrador Junior Ingredients: Rice; dehydrated poultry protein; maize; vegetable protein isolate*; maize gluten; animal fats; hydrolysed animal proteins; minerals; beet pulp; fish oil; vegetable fibres; soya oil; fructo-oligo-saccharides; psyllium husks and seeds; hydrolysed yeast (source of mannooligo-saccharides); hydrolysed crustaceans (source of glucosamine); borage oil; marigold extract (source of lutein); hydrolysed cartilage (source of chondroitin).Analysis:Protein: 33%; Fat content: 14%; Crude ash: 7.3%; Crude fibres: 1.7%; Calcium: 9;9 g/kg; Phosphorus: 8;3 g/kg.

left_name: Royal Canin Beagle Adult 12kg
left_descrtiption: Royal Canin Beagle Adult 12kgBeagle Adult 12 months + Complete feed for dogs - Specially for adult and mature Beagles - Over 12 months old. Benefits include IdealWeight Formula; Exclusively Kibble; Bone and Joint Support; Food intake control;IDEAL WEIGHTThe Beagle is known for his tendency to gain weight. This formula helps maintain the Beagle’s ideal weight thanks to an adapted calorie content.FOOD INTAKE CONTROLThe kibble’s exclusive shape helps reduce the rate of food intake and encourage chewing. This formula also contains a combination of fibres.BONE AND JOINT HEALTHThis specific formula helps support healthy bones and joints and maintain ideal weight. Enriched with EPA & DHA.EXCLUSIVE KIBBLEThe kibble’s texture and formula are adapted to the Beagle dog.IngredientsCOMPOSITION: dehydrated poultry protein; maize; rice; wheat; animal fats; maize gluten; hydrolysed animal proteins; vegetable fibres; vegetable protein isolate*; beet pulp; minerals; fish oil; yeasts; soya oil; psyllium husks and seeds; fructo-oligo-saccharides; hydrolysed yeast (source of manno-oligo-saccharides); borage oil; green tea and grape extracts (source of polyphenols); hydrolysed crustaceans (source of glucosamine); marigold extract (source of lutein); hydrolysed cartilage (source of chondroitin). ADDITIVES (per kg): Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 28000 IU; Vitamin D3: 700 IU; E1 (Iron): 42 mg; E2 (Iodine): 4.2 mg; E4 (Copper): 5 mg; E5 (Manganese): 55 mg; E6 (Zinc): 164 mg; E8(Selenium): 0.09 mg - Preservatives - Antioxidants. ANALYTICAL CONSTITUENTS: Protein: 27% - Fat content: 12% - Crude ash: 6.1% - Crude fibres: 3.7% - EPA and DHA fatty acids: 3 g/kg.

right_descrtiption: Royal Canin German Shepherd Junior dry dog food has been specially developed to meet the individual nutritional needs of your growing dog. As they age; young German Shepherds go through an important growth phase; which must be kept at a stable rate to help prevent later health problems. This complete dry food is intended to promote balanced growth in junior German Shepherds up to 15 months old. Alongside maintaining a steady growth rate; Royal Canin Breed German Shepherd Junior helps to promote your dog's intestinal health and boost their natural defences. Your growing dog will also benefit from additional skin and coat protection thanks to the careful blend of vitamins and amino acids.  German Shepherds have a truly noble character that makes them popular both as a working dog and as a domestic companion. They are also incredibly strong and handsome dogs; boasting powerful muscles and a well-developed chest. Royal Canin Junior German Shepherd bears all of these breed characteristics in mind; guaranteeing a dry dog food that meets all of your dog's nutritional requirements. Royal Canin German Shepherd Junior:Optimal digestive security: Rice as a single source of plant carbohydrates; high-grade L.I.P. proteins (>90%) and soya bean oil all contribute to a healthy digestive system. Select; special fibres limit the fermentation process in the digestive tract; while maintaining the balance of the intestinal flora.Strengthening the immune system and reducing oxidative stress: An antioxidant complex contributes to the strengthening of the immune system and slows cell ageing. Mannan-oligosaccharides stimulate a response from the immune system; which raises the quantity of antibodies (immunoglobulin A; white blood cells).  Skin protection and radiant fur: Royal Canin Breed German Shepherd Junior dog food strengthens the barrier function of the skin and maintains the natural shine of your dog's fur with a mixture of vitamins and amino acids.Joint protection and balanced growth: The synergistic effect of chrondroitin sulphate and glucosamines protects the joints and helps to slow the development of arthritis; inflammation and oxidative damage with the help of omega-3 fatty acids EPA and DHAKibble:

right_descrtiption: Taste of the Wild – Southwest Canyon combines beef; wild boar; fish and lamb to provide a high-protein unique dry food bound to be loved by every dog; no matter what breed; age or size. It is ideal for sensitive dogs as it does not use grain products; making it highly-digestible. This recipe also contains peas; which can be a vital source of vitamins; trace elements and other important nutrients. Another great source of these nutrients is the range of fruit and vegetables in this wholesome kibble; which also provide antioxidants and help maximise immune system function. The digestive system is also supported; thanks to inulin found in chicory and an ingredient called yucca schidigera. Every ingredient meets extremely high quality standards and has been designed to give your dog an enjoyable and flavourful eating experience.Taste of the Wild - Southwest Canyon dry dog food at a glance:Suitable for all dogs; no matter what age; breed or sizeA unique blend of meat proteins: A combination of delicious ingredients designed to provide your dog with health-conscious sources of energy; protein and fat.Grain-free: Many dogs struggle with digesting grains and find that they can result in adverse reactions. This food does not use any kinds of grain; making it much easier to digest and much healthier for your dog.Peas: Provide carbohydrates and other vital minerals.Perfect for sensitive dogs.A variety of sources: This unique combination of meats provides an optimum balance of amino acids; including ocean-sourced fish which gives your dog omega-3 fatty acids; great for keeping coats gleaming.Eggs: Provide highly-digestible proteins including lutein and zeaxanthin for eyesight support.Linseed: Rich in fatty acids and mucilage; for healthy coat and digestionAntioxidant-rich: For the neutralisation of free radicalsHealthy digestive system: An optimum intestinal environment is developed; thanks to chicory; yucca schidigera and inulin.Omega fatty-acids: omega-3 and -6 fatty acids can be beneficial for your dog's overall health.Raspberries and blueberries: Offer antioxidants in the form of phytonutrientsFree from: vegetable or animal by-products; waste products from slaughterhouses and additives such as flavourings.Tomatoes: For dietary fibre; lycopene and beta-carotene.All Life-Stages Nutrition: The AAFCO (Association of American Feed Control Officials) provide guidelines for the best way to meet your dog's nutritional needs at every point in its life; and this food meets those needs.Taste of the Wild – Southwest Canyon is a dry dog food ideal for all dogs; and is dog food just as nature intended.

right_descrtiption: Royal Canin Mini Dermacomfort is a unique food that can help small dogs that suffer from skin irritation. Healthy skin is vital to ensuring your dog’s wellbeing; as it forms a barrier which protects the organs; and prevents the body from drying out. It also protects the body from injury and infections from harmful bacteria; as well as storing fats and vitamins and being an important source of sensory information.Itching; dandruff; a greasy coat or dry skin are all signs that something may be wrong with your dog. These complaints can affect your dog’s overall wellbeing; so they should not be ignored. Royal Canin Mini Dermacomfort has a combination of active ingredients designed to combat skin complaints and improve the skin’s health. Royal Canin Mini Dermacomfort dog food contains a unique combination of nutrients and a patented complex to improve and keep your dog’s fur and skin healthy. After only one month of feeding your dog Royal Canin Dermacomfort you will notice an improvement; with less scratching and itching.Royal Canin Health Nutrition - know and respect your dog's behavioural and nutritional requirements to ensure its wellbeing and health. The benefits of Royal Canin Mini Dermacomfort at a glance:For small dogs with sensitive skinKeeps skin healthySupports the skin’s barrier roleWith valuable omega-3- and omega-6 fatty acids which have a positive effect on skin and furWith selected; highly digestible protein sources which are for dogs with sensitive skinReduces skin irritation and itchingReduces skin issues. Visible results achieved after only one month of feedingLess scratching and itching

right_name: Taste of the Wild Appalachian Valley Adult Small Breed
right_descrtiption: Royal Canin Golden Retriever Junior dry dog food is made according to a delicious recipe that provides all the nutrients your young dog needs during this important life stage. As they age; junior Golden Retrievers go through a sensitive growth period that can have a significant impact upon their health in later life. Nutritional deficiencies at a young age can lead to a range of health conditions in adulthood; so it is vital that your growing Golden Retriever receives special dietary care. Royal Canin Breed Golden Retriever Junior is the ideal balanced diet for young Golden Retrievers up to 15 months old; helping to protect the health of your dog's joints and provide important support for their natural immune system.Golden Retrievers are well-loved for their friendly and trusting nature; which makes them an excellent family dog. Their distinctive soft and glossy coat features a water-repellent undercoat; which requires particular care and protection. Golden Retrievers also have highly sensitive skin; meaning they need special nutritional support to help strengthen their skin's resistance to allergens and inflammation. Royal Canin Junior Golden Retriever has been developed with these breed characteristics in mind; so you can be sure that you are feeding your growing Golden Retriever the best possible diet.Royal Canin Golden Retriever Junior:Glossy coat: The combination of borage oil and biotine promotes a soft and shiny coat. Sulphureous amino acids enhance the production of keratin and support fur growth. The combination of pantothenic acid; niacin; inositol and choline strengthens skin-resistance.         A strong immune system:  An antioxidant complex strengthens the natural defences and counteracts cell ageing; while mannan-oligosaccharides stimulate immune reactions by increasing the number of antibodies. Joint protection: The synergistic effect of chondroitin sulphate and glucosamine protects the joints; supports harmonious bone development and slows down the development of arthritis. Omega-3 fatty acids EPA and DHA fight inflammations and oxidative damage. Digestive security: Rice is used as the only source of plant-based carbohydrate; while highly digestible proteins help to keep the intestinal flora balanced and healthy.   Kibble:

Golden Retrievers also have highly sensitive skin; meaning they need special nutritional support to help strengthen their skin's resistance to allergens and inflammation. Royal Canin Junior Golden Retriever has been developed with these breed characteristics in mind; so you can be sure that you are feeding your growing Golden Retriever the best possible diet.Royal Canin Golden Retriever Junior:Glossy coat: The combination of borage oil and biotine promotes a soft and shiny coat. Sulphureous amino acids enhance the production of keratin and support fur growth. The combination of pantothenic acid; niacin; inositol and choline strengthens skin-resistance.         A strong immune system:  An antioxidant complex strengthens the natural defences and counteracts cell ageing; while mannan-oligosaccharides stimulate immune reactions by increasing the number of antibodies. Joint protection: The synergistic effect of chondroitin sulphate and glucosamine protects the joints; supports harmonious bone development and slows down the development of arthritis. Omega-3 fatty acids EPA and DHA fight inflammations and oxidative damage. Digestive security: Rice is used as the only source of plant-based carbohydrate; while highly digestible proteins help to keep the intestinal flora balanced and healthy.   Kibble:

left_descrtiption: This Royal Canin West Highland White Terrier Adult is the ideal way to keep skin and fur in fabulous condition. West Highland White Terriers are sturdy dogs that were initially used for hunting in the Highlands; meaning that they are accustomed to unpleasant weather. However; it also means that they do not shed their coats and need regular grooming and trimming to keep them looking their best. Their small jaws also require extra care; as their teeth are placed closely together and need to be closely cared for to combat tartar build up.These particular characteristics have all been considered in the production of this Royal Canin West Highland White Terrier Adult dry dog food; which is suitable for terriers over the age of 10 months:Glossy white fur: West Highland White Terriers have sensitive skin and thick coats; which need extra care. right_descrtiption: Taste of the Wild - Pacific Stream Puppy is a delicious grain-free delight for any breed of growing dog. This balanced recipe has been developed from the natural diets of dogs in the wild; full of everything your dog could need to live a happy and healthy lifestyle. Sweet potatoes are the carbohydrate source in this dry food; something that is much easier to digest than grains and cereals; which can lead to adverse reactions and make mealtimes an unpleasant experience for sensitive dogs. As well as being a healthy source of carbohydrate; they also provide vital vitamins such as calcium; beta-carotene and iron; and act as a source of dietary fibre. This tasty dish uses fish as its only source of protein; which adds to its already high digestibility. Salmon not only acts as a premium protein but also as a source of omega-3 fatty acids such as DHA; which are known to help with eyesight and brain development; which are naturally of the utmost importance in a growing puppy. They can also keep joints moving smoothly and coat gleaming and in tip-top condition. Inulin; yucca schidigera and chicory all work to promote healthy digestive function. Every ingredient in this food is designed to keep your dog's health at the highest possible standard; providing all necessary nutrients and even acting as a source of antioxidants to increase immune system function. A luxurious culinary delight for even the most sensitive of dogs.Taste of the Wild - Pacific Stream Puppy dry dog food at a glance:Suitable for any breed and ideal for puppies. Ideal for sensitive dogs suffering from dietary intolerance or allergic reactions to particular proteins and/or grain.Mono-source protein: By using just one source of protein; this food becomes extremely well accepted and highly-digestible.With tasty salmon: For premium protein and essential omega-3 fatty acids. Highly-digestible and delicious. Grain-free: Grain can often lead to unpleasant adverse reactions; which is why this food contains none. Grain is also high in carbohydrate; which can lead to innumerable unpleasant issues with health. By avoiding grain; this dry food provides your dog with a healthy all-round nutrition.Omega fatty acids: Omega-3 and -6 fatty acids give your dog healthy skin and glossy coat.Sweet Potatoes: Ultra nutritious and highly-digestible; they are packed full of fibre; as well as being a source of vitamins such as calcium; beta-carotene and iron.Raspberries and blueberries: Contain antioxidants in the form of phytonutrients; to help neutralise free radicals.Tomatoes: Full of vegetable fibre to promote digestion and packed with vitamins and antioxidants; including lycopene and beta-carotene.Free from: Animal and vegetable by-products; waste products from the slaughterhouse and artificial flavourings and colourings. All Life-Stages Nutrition: Taste of the Wild dog food has been designed to continue meeting your dog's needs at every point in its life; according to the AAFCO (Association of American Feed Control Officials) recommendations.Taste of the Wild – Pacific Stream Puppy dog food is ideal for junior dogs and puppies of any breed - dog food just as nature intended.

left_name: Hill's Prescription Diet Canine i/d Digestive Care
left_descrtiption: Hill's Prescription Diet Canine i/d Digestive Care with Chicken complete dry dog food has been formulated to help relieve digestive upset caused by canine gastrointestinal disorders; as well as to improve digestion in dogs that suffer from exocrine pancreatic insufficiency. This highly digestible; complete dog food has a low fat content and is therefore ideal for feeding as a recovery diet after surgery or a debilitating illness. The dietetic recipe features high levels of electrolytes and vital antioxidants; which can have a positive impact on your dog’s general health.Hill's Prescription Diet Canine i/d Digestive Care with Chicken has been developed by specialists for junior and adult dogs that suffer from gastrointestinal disorders; providing them with a balanced ratio of all vital nutrients they need. Indications:Acute and chronic gastrointestinal disorders; including gastritis; enteritis; colitis (the most common causes of  diarrhoea; malabsorption and bacterial overgrowth)Recovery after intestinal-related surgeryRecovery after minor surgery or other debilitating diseasesExocrine pancreatic insufficiencyAcute pancreatitisBloating (gastric dilatation and volvulus)Meets the needs of growing junior dogsContraindications:Dogs with sodium retentionCatsHill's™ Prescription Diet™ has a wide selection of clinically proven nutritional products which meet your pet's specific dietary needs. Hill's Evidence-Based Clinical Nutrition™ uses the most up-to-date scientific research evidence combined with clinical expertise to develop a range of diets which help alleviate your pet’s health issues.Please consult your vet for further information and specific treatment options for your pet. 100% satisfaction guaranteed: Hill´s Prescription Diet products are made using only top quality ingredients. They have a delicious taste your pet will love. Hill's are so confident that your pet will enjoy Hill´s Prescription Diet foods that they offer a 100% money-back guarantee.

left_name: Royal Canin Mini Adult
left_descrtiption: Royal Canin Mini Adult is suitable for all small breed dogs with an adult weight up to 10kg; aged 10 months and over. Small breed dogs are often fussy about what they eat. This kibble is made with easy to digest tasty ingredients which will appeal to your little dog. It is also enriched with EPA DHA fatty acids which help to keep your pet’s fur healthy and shiny. Many small dogs suffer with sensitive skin and this dry food can help to keep it supple and smooth.Many small dogs have a tendency to put on weight and over a third of all small dogs are overweight. Obesity can affect your pet’s health so Royal Canin Mini Adult has been formulated to meet the increased energy demands of small dogs while helping to maintain the ideal weight. It also contains L-carnitine which promotes fat metabolism.Royal Canin Mini Adult aids good dental hygiene. Small dogs have small jaws so their teeth are close together. This makes their teeth the ideal place for bacteria and left over bits of food and this can lead to dental tartar. The chelation agents in calcium can help to reduce tartar formation.Royal Canin Mini Adult:
left_price: Tartar reduction: sodium polyphosphates bind salivary calcium which helps to limit tartar development
right_id: Skin and coat: vitamins and amino acids improve the skin's barrier function and prevent the bacteria from penetrating. Vitamin A; biotin; fish oil; linoleic acid and zinc all help to promote a shiny coat and reduced scurf development
right_name: Enhanced palatability: carefully selected nutrients and natural flavours ensure maximum acceptance. Special texture; shape and size of kibble help satisfy fussy appetites
